restly.exceptions.redirection

Class HttpRedirectionException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • restly.exceptions.HttpStatusException
          • restly.exceptions.redirection.HttpRedirectionException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FoundException, MovedPermanentlyException, MultipleChoicesException, NotModifiedException, SeeOtherException, TemporaryRedirectException, UseProxyException

    public class HttpRedirectionException
extends HttpStatusException
    3xx Redirection

    This class of status code indicates that further action needs to be taken by the user agent in order to fulfill the request. The action required MAY be carried out by the user agent without interaction with the user if and only if the method used in the second request is GET or HEAD. A client SHOULD detect infinite redirection loops, since such loops generate network traffic for each redirection.

    Author:
    Erik Beeson
    See Also:
    http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2616#section-10.3, Serialized Form
